BY HARRIET CHIKANDIWA
By-elections to fill vacant seats in the National Assembly will be held on March 26 President Mnangagwa has announced. The announcement was made in Proclamation 1 of 2022 published under Statutory Instrument 2 of 2022.  Several seats have been vacant following the recall or death of sitting legislators. “Now therefore under and by virtue of the powers vested in the President as afore said, I do, by this proclamation (a) order new elections for the afore-mentioned order new elections for the aforementioned Constituencies; and fix Wednesday the 26th day of January, 2022, as the date on which the nomination courts shall sit, commencing at 10 o’clock in the morning,” “Fix Saturday the 26th day of March, 2022 as the day on which a [poll shall be taken or a poll becomes necessary in terms of section 46(17) of the Electoral Act,” read the SI.